params.amountOut_: The amount of the last token to receive
params.path_: The path of the swap, i.e. each token pair and the pool fee. Path must be provided in reverse order

returns.amountIn: The amount of first token required to be paid
returns.amountInMaximum: The amount of first token required to be paid with slippage

returns._0: address The address of the Uniswap V3 Router

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

returns._0: tokenPrice The price of the token derived from the pool's slot0 information

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params.uniswapQuoter_: The address of the Uniswap V3 Quoter
params.uniswapV3Router_: The address of the Uniswap V3 Router
params.wethAddress_: The address of the WETH token

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params.slippage_: Slippage value represented in wei (1e17 means 10% slippage allowance)

params.amountInMaximum_: Maximum amount of liquid tokens to be used for the swap
params.assetsAmount_: Amount of asset tokens to be received
params.liquidTokenAddress_: Address of the liquid token to be swapped
params.receiver_: Address that will receive the swapped tokens

returns._0: address asset address and the amount of assets transferred
returns._1: uint256 asset address and the amount of assets transferred

VAULT_STRATEGY_ROLE().notice: VAULT STRATEGY ROLE to manage configuration and execution

claimEarnings(address,address).notice: Unimplemented claim earnings function to fulfill IAdapter interface

deposit(address,address,address,uint256,.notice: Unimplemented deposit function to fulfill IAdapter interface

getAmountInForexactOutput(bytes,uint256).notice: Returns the amount in required for a given exact output swap without executing the swap

getProtocol().notice: Retrieves the protocol address being used (Uniswap V3 Router)

getSlippage().notice: Retrieves the currently configured slippage value

getTokenPrice(address).notice: Retrieves the current token price using the configured pool

initialize(address,address,address).notice: Initializes the Uniswap V3 adapter with necessary contract addresses

poolsPerTokenForPrice(address).notice: Mapping to store pool address of each token to get the price

setPoolPerTokenForPrice(address,address).notice: Set the pool address to get price for a specific token

setSlippage(uint256).notice: Sets new slippage allowance value for scaling operations

setUniswapQuoterAddress(address).notice: Updates the address of the Uniswap V3 Quoter

setUniswapRouterAddress(address).notice: Updates the address of the Uniswap V3 Router

uniswapQuoter().notice: Address of the Uniswap V3 Quoter used for obtaining quotes

uniswapV3Router().notice: Address of the Uniswap V3 Router used for swaps

withdraw(address,address,address,uint256.notice: Withdraws tokens by swapping them on Uniswap V3
